Package: dforge
Version: 0.1.0-1
Section: vcs
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libssl3, ca-certificates
Maintainer: Harish <mailtoharish200@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/harishannavisamy/dforge
Description: Serverless decentralized Git on IPFS + Blockchain
 DecentraForge (dforge) is a serverless, decentralized version control
 system that combines Git semantics with IPFS content-addressed storage
 and Ethereum blockchain access control.
 .
 No central server required. Repositories are encrypted with AES-256-GCM,
 keys are split using Shamir Secret Sharing (2-of-3 threshold), and
 commits are signed with Ed25519.
 .
 Features: init, commit, branch, merge, push/pull via IPFS, pull requests,
 issues, trigram code search, and a lazygit-style TUI.
